The problem is with `impsort-maven-plugin` plugin should declare dependencies on `plexus-utils` if use it.

With Maven 3.8.x and older `plexus-utils` was always added to plugin classpath - [MNG-6965][1]

You can check if newer version of `impsort-maven-plugin` is available with fixes, if no you can add dependencies to plexus-utils for plugin in your project.

eg:

```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;plugin.groupId&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;impsort-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;xxx&lt;/version&gt;
  &lt;dependencies&gt;
    &lt;dependency&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;org.codehaus.plexus&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;plexus-utils&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;3.5.1&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;
  &lt;/dependencies&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```





  [1]: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-6965

