You&#39;re using the JMS API incorrectly. As noted in the JavaDoc both `setJMSPriority` and `setJMSExpiration` **cannot** be used by the client application. These are only to be used by the JMS provider itself. See [here][1] for priority:

&gt; This method is for use by **JMS providers only** to set this field when a message is sent. This message **cannot be used by clients** to configure the priority level of the message. This method is public to allow a JMS provider to set this field when sending a message whose implementation is not its own.

And [here][2] for expiration:

&gt; This method is for use by **JMS providers only** to set this field when a message is sent. This message **cannot be used by clients** to configure the expiration time of the message. This method is public to allow a JMS provider to set this field when sending a message whose implementation is not its own.

You can use the [`setPriority(int)`][3] and [`setTimeToLive(long)`][4] methods of `MessageProducer` instead, e.g.:
```java
public class SendMessageTest {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        QueueConnection connection = null;
        InitialContext initialContext = null;
        try {
            initialContext = new InitialContext();
            QueueConnectionFactory cf = new ActiveMQQueueConnectionFactory(&quot;tcp://localhost:61616&quot;);
            Queue queue = (Queue) initialContext.lookup(&quot;dynamicQueues/&quot; + &quot;exampleQueue&quot;);
            connection = cf.createQueueConnection();
            QueueSession session = connection.createQueueSession(false, Session.AUTO_ACKNOWLEDGE);
            MessageProducer producer = session.createProducer(queue);
            producer.setPriority(7);
            producer.setTimeToLive(600000);
            TextMessage message = session.createTextMessage(&quot;This is a text message&quot;);
            message.setJMSCorrelationID(&quot;3445125584339&quot;);
            message.setJMSReplyTo(queue);
            producer.send(message);
            System.out.println(&quot;Sent message: &quot; + message.getText());
        } catch (NamingException | JMSException e) {
            System.out.println(e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}
```


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/Message.html#setJMSPriority-int-
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/Message.html#setJMSExpiration-long-
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/MessageProducer.html#setPriority-int-
  [4]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/MessageProducer.html#setTimeToLive-long-

