First, note you have a syntax error in your CSS file:

    -fx-stroke = green;

should be

    -fx-stroke: green;

Additionally, note from the [documentation](https://openjfx.io/javadoc/20/javafx.graphics/javafx/scene/doc-files/cssref.html#line) that the style class of `Line` is empty by default. (Only `Control` and its subclasses, along with `ImageView`, `WebView`, and `MediaView` have default style classes.) Consequently, the selector will not select the line. You can either add the style class to the line explicitly:

        Line l = new Line(10,10,90,90);
        l.getStyleClass().add(&quot;line&quot;);

or us a Type Selector. From the documentation:

&gt;Node&#39;s getTypeSelector method returns a String which is analogous to a CSS Type Selector. By default, this method returns the simple name of the class. 

So the following will work without adding the style class in the Java code:

    Line {
    -fx-stroke: green;
    
    }

